cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.IR

The paper discusses the privacy and security risks associated with the leak of personal data, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The analysis of the leaked dataset involves processing and identifying personal information, which is related to database systems (cs.DB). The use of automated processing techniques to extract information from the leaked dataset also involves aspects of cybercrime (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the need for stricter measures to protect the privacy and security of individuals, which is related to system and information security (cs.SI).
